This paper is about the results and analysis of an international planning competition, which involves the use of artificial intelligence (AI) techniques to solve planning and scheduling problems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also includes statistical analysis of the results, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the paper discusses challenges for the future of the competition series, which may be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.PL (Programming Languages).
